A 91-year-old gogo crashed her luxury car into a streetlight and poles, while she was allegedly drunk. After that the police conducted two breathalyser tests at the scene and she failed the tests. She was then arrested and taken to a police station. According to the Mirror, the gogo was driving her A3 Sportback through Colchester in Essex southeast England, when she lost control while she was drunk. The cops said she admitted to drunk-driving and pledged to give up her car when her 14-month ban expires. The gogo will stop driving after a shocking 76 years behind the wheel. “She was recorded with a 47 micrograms of alcohol in 100ml of breath – over the legal limit of 35.”